## 1. Purpose
This policy defines how long [COMPANY] retains different categories of data and how data and the media that hold it are securely disposed of when no longer needed. It ensures retention satisfies legal, regulatory, and contractual obligations (including HIPAA documentation retention) while minimizing the risk of holding data — especially PHI — longer than necessary. Secure disposal ensures retired data cannot be recovered.

## 2. Scope
Applies to all [COMPANY] data and storage media in any form across all in-scope systems, explicitly including the production SaaS application, [AWS] storage and databases, [Snowflake], **backups and snapshots**, [GitHub] repositories and logs, endpoints, and any physical media (paper, drives). It binds all workforce members and is coordinated with vendors holding [COMPANY] data (`../vendor/third-party-risk-management-policy.md.template`).

## 3. Policy
1. Data **shall** be retained only as long as required by legal, regulatory, contractual, or legitimate business need, then securely disposed of.
2. **HIPAA-required documentation** — policies and procedures, risk analyses, breach assessments, training records, access logs and other required records — **shall** be retained for at least **six (6) years** from the date of creation or the date last in effect, whichever is later (45 CFR § 164.316(b)(2)).
3. Retention periods for **PHI/health records and customer data** **shall** be set per the schedule in §5, informed by applicable **state law and customer/BAA contractual** requirements (which often exceed six years), confirmed with counsel.
4. Data under a **legal hold** **shall** be preserved and **shall not** be disposed of until the hold is released, overriding the schedule.
5. Disposal of media and data **shall** meet recognized **sanitization standards (NIST SP 800-88)** appropriate to the media and classification (§6); PHI requires secure destruction or cryptographic erasure.
6. Disposal of Restricted/PHI data **shall** be documented (what, when, method, by whom) to evidence destruction.
7. Cloud data deletion **shall** account for replicas, **backups, and snapshots** so that "deleted" PHI is not silently retained beyond its period.
8. Disposal performed by vendors **shall** be governed by contract and, for PHI, a BAA, with a certificate/attestation of destruction obtained where practical.

## 4. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Owns this policy; oversees secure disposal; verifies sanitization methods. |
| [General Counsel / Privacy Officer] | Sets/confirms retention periods and legal holds; confirms HIPAA/state obligations. |
| Data / Asset Owners | Apply retention to data they own; initiate disposal; retain disposal records. |
| [IT / Platform Team] | Execute deletion across [AWS]/[Snowflake]/backups; sanitize/destroy media. |
| All Workforce | Do not retain Restricted data beyond need; do not dispose of records under hold. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template`.

