## 6. Secure Disposal & Media Sanitization
Disposal method is chosen per media type and data classification, aligned to **NIST SP 800-88**:

| Scenario / Media | Method |
|---|---|
| Cloud-stored data ([AWS S3/RDS], [Snowflake] tables) | Logical deletion + ensure removal from **replicas, backups, and snapshots**; rely on provider sanitization for underlying storage |
| Encrypted data | **Cryptographic erase** (destroy/rotate keys so data is unrecoverable) where supported |
| SSD / flash | Cryptographic erase or vendor secure-erase; physical destruction for highly sensitive |
| Magnetic drives | Secure overwrite (NIST 800-88 Clear/Purge) or physical destruction |
| End-of-life endpoints | Wipe/cryptographic erase via [MDM] before reuse; destroy if it held Restricted data and cannot be verified clean |
| Paper / physical media | Cross-cut shredding or certified destruction |

**For Restricted/PHI:** prefer Purge or Destroy; record a disposal/destruction log entry (item, date, method, performed by, witness/attestation).

## 7. Cloud & Backup Considerations
Because [AWS] and [Snowflake] replicate data and retain **backups, snapshots, and time-travel/fail-safe copies**, "deleting" PHI from a primary store does not by itself complete disposal. Disposal **shall** account for: backup/snapshot lifecycles, [Snowflake] Time Travel/Fail-safe windows, log copies, and any exports. The [Platform Team] confirms data has aged out of all copies within its retention window.

## 8. Exceptions
Exceptions to this policy require documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by [Security Officer] and [General Counsel], time-bound, and recorded in the exceptions log. Legal holds always override exceptions.

## 9. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
The [Security Officer] verifies that retention and disposal occur per schedule and that disposal records exist for Restricted data. Improper disposal of PHI may constitute an impermissible disclosure and trigger `../healthcare/hipaa-breach-notification-procedure.md.template`. Violations are handled per `../people/hr-security-policy.md.template`.

